 and I tell you why:

Pros:
+ Fun arcade gameplay;
+ Destructible environment;
+ Very high focused in teamwork and tactics;
+ Operators have unique habilities that can change the game and the way you play.

Cons:
- The same problems of closed and open beta remains;
- Matchmaking issues (you will be waiting way more than playing);
- Menus and weapon customization feels clunky;
- No campaign;
- Very low content for the full price;
- Microtransactions (for weapon skins and XP boosters) even with paid DLC;
- Lots of bugs (like graphic glitches

reviewText:
The game has so much potential.

But:
- tons of hackers and Ubi's unwillingness to do anything about it;
- terrible netcode;
- rather limited content for the price;
- countless bugs.

make me unwilling to recommend it to anyone on full price. [to all the previous commenantators: FULL PRICE was kinda a key thing].

Other than that if you are willing to occasionally rage about newly introduced bugs and still terrible netcode - give it a try to enjoy:
- well done maps (although there are quite a few of them);
- rather mature community;
- well thought mechanics;
- tactical nature of the shooter;
- almost addictive replayability.

P.S. Don't buy a season pass.

Overall great game with extremely interesting teamwork and highly satisfying gunplay that is very hard to enjoy because of the abundance of irritating server-side problems and issues that are slowly killing this game, including:
•infinite data synchronization after nearly every match, players cannot get their rewards;
•infinite loadings while connecting to an active match with Alt-F4 as the only solution to unfreeze the game;
•friend invites may bug the game so you need to restart it if you want to play with your comrades;
•people can get stuck in empty rooms, walls, railings, placeable items or just in scattered junk - seeing that if it happens, it happens with all players, this is also a server-side problem;
•matchmaking takes A LOT of time;
•random connectivity errors with uninformative codes that kicks you out of the game or do other nasty crap (like deny you to play certain gamemode)...
I really want to recommend this game, it's fun and challenging, but I won't until Ubisoft upgrades their ♥♥♥♥♥♥ antique servers. Wait if you want to buy it.

Some people will say TC universe is turning into a multiplayer madness for sells because of UBI but to be honest this Rainbow Six feels refreshing and good and even thought it kills some of the immersive feels the old ones in the series had, it brings to us a new perspective and one of the best team play experiences i ever had on games.

+ The co-op;

+ Casual mode so you don't feel absurd crushed playing against competitive/pro players;

+ Match making features;

+ The creative ways for demolition or stealth approaches;

+ The built for team play and communication;

+ It uses the FPS genre to it's best bringing the intensity and adrenaline i wish all games had;

+ Classes! It's so good to be able to choose among so many classes that will also be expanded on future DLCs;

+ The multi platform! You can link your Uplay account on the R6 site and use the white boards to create new methods and tactics with your squad/friends;
And even thought this game offers a lot and is a revitalizing new path for Rainbow Six and MP games it ofc has some downfalls, such as:
- The short single player career, i know not the focus of the game, still could have at least a SP level for each operator no need to even change maps just new approaches and SP ways to train environments and tactics;

- Sometimes i feel like this game still on development, right now we suffering with huge hit detection issues. The Ubi servers are also always kicking someone out of the match so if you have a party of five embrace for long lobby minutes and restarting searches because someone fell out;

- The season pass as for now is just a title the 5% boost is exactly what it seems...5% no big deal there. The gold in store gave to us is just 600 in game currency, the equivalent to having a nickel in fancy store. The plus challenges are not two per day...and so goes on. Now waiting for the chance to have access to early operators before the ones without season pass but still will have to use game renown to unblock those;

- THE OPEN MIC BUG!

- The community still small and is understandable that not everyone is friendly but if you really want the game feel of team play you have to bring your own friends or have luck to find some in between random teammates;TL;DR: This game still has a lot to offer and i hope they deliver it, aside the bugs and the 'under construction' feel the game is genuinely one of the best experiences i ever had on the multiplayer/co-op genre.

If i have to bet on it's future i'll sure do.

08/10 as good as the enemy cluster charge on the hostage;

